      <h2 id="frequently-asked-questions"><a href="#frequently-asked-questions"></a>FAQ - Häufig gestellte Fragen</h2>
      <p>
        This page lists frequently asked questions and answers. If you are new to the page, you might find some
        helpful tips here. However, if you struggle with anything not discussed on this page, send us an email.
      </p>

      <h3 id="what-does-grouping-do"><a href="#what-does-grouping-do"></a>Was macht Gruppierung?</h3>
      <p>
        You can toggle between a chronological or grouped table view. When viewing the incoming radio calls in 
        chronological mode, every call will created a new entry on top of the table. This creates a log file
        of every recorded call.
      </p>
      <p>
        Alternatively, when switching to the grouped view, the page works similar to a voice chat app like
        Skype, Teams, Discord or Teamspeak. When a call is made, existing table entries are reused. Instead
        of creating a growing log of every call, only the last call made per user is visible.
      </p>

